Real-Life Connections: String Manipulation
1. Auto-capitalizing names
Programs use functions like capitalize() or title() to automatically change the first letter of a name to uppercase before saving it.

2. Checking password length
Programs use a length function (such as len()) to count the characters and check if the password meets the required length.

3. Separating an address
Programs use split() to divide the address into parts like barangay, municipality, province, and zip code based on spaces.

4. Standardizing names
Programs convert all names to lowercase using lower() and then apply title() so all names follow the same format.

